      • continueParsing

        public Command continueParsing​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> parameters)
                        throws DuchessException
        Continues the parsing of user input from extracted parameters.

        This function is called when there are consecutive state transitions within a single parse call.

        Parameters:
        parameters - the parameterized user input
        Returns:
        the command to execute
        Throws:
        DuchessException - if the user input is invalid
